'''ᱠᱚᱯᱤᱞ ᱥᱟᱨᱢᱟ''' (ᱡᱟᱱᱟᱢ ᱒ ᱚᱯᱨᱮᱞ ᱑᱙᱘᱑)<ref name="DOB">{{Cite news |url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/telly-talk/gossip/article/kapil-sharma-37-birthday-sunil-grover-wish-on-twitter/213287 |title=After Twitter war, Sunil Grover wishes his 'brother' Kapil Sharma a happy birthday |last=Banerjee |first=Anindita |date=2 April 2018 |work=[[Times Now]] |access-date=16 December 2018}}</ref> ᱫᱚ ᱢᱤᱫ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛᱤᱭᱟ‌. [[ᱥᱴᱟᱱᱰ ᱚᱯ ᱠᱚᱢᱮᱰᱤ|ᱥᱴᱟᱱᱰ ᱚᱯ ᱠᱚᱢᱮᱰᱤᱭᱟᱱ]], ᱴᱮᱞᱤᱵᱤᱡᱚᱱ ᱯᱨᱮᱡᱮᱱᱴᱚᱨ, ᱟᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱟᱨ ᱯᱨᱚᱰᱭᱩᱥᱚᱨ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱾ ᱱᱩᱭ ᱫᱚ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱠᱚᱢᱮᱰᱤ ᱥᱳ ''[[ᱫᱤ ᱠᱚᱯᱤᱞ ᱥᱚᱨᱢᱟ ᱥᱳ]]'' ᱠᱷᱟ.ᱛᱤᱨ ᱦᱚᱲ ᱴᱷᱮᱱ ᱵᱷᱟ.ᱜᱤ ᱞᱮᱠᱟ ᱵᱟᱰᱟᱭ ᱟᱠᱟᱱ ᱾<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/kapil-sharma-i-will-do-as-ginni-says-because-i-know-that-she-is-right/articleshow/66794849.cms|title=Kapil Sharma: I will do as Ginni says, because I know that she is right - Times of India|website=The Times of India|accessdate=10 December 2019}}</ref> ᱩᱱᱤ ᱫᱚ ᱯᱩᱭᱞᱩ [[ᱠᱟᱢᱮᱰᱤ ᱱᱟᱭᱤᱴᱥ ᱣᱤᱛᱷ ᱠᱚᱯᱤᱞ]] ᱟᱨ [[ᱯᱷᱮᱢᱤᱞᱤ ᱴᱟᱭᱤᱢ ᱣᱤᱛᱷ ᱠᱚᱯᱤᱞ]] ᱴᱮᱞᱤᱵᱤᱡᱟᱱ ᱥᱳ ᱨᱮ ᱦᱚᱸᱭ ᱦᱳᱥᱴ ᱟᱠᱟᱫᱟ ᱾ ᱒᱐᱑᱖ ᱚᱯᱨᱮᱞ ᱨᱮ, ᱠᱚᱯᱤᱞ ᱫᱚ ᱟ.ᱰᱤ ᱧᱩᱛᱩᱢᱟᱱ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛᱤᱭᱟ. ᱴᱮᱞᱤᱵᱤᱡᱚᱱ ᱟᱠᱴᱚᱨ ᱠᱟᱱᱟᱭ ᱢᱮᱱᱛᱮ ᱳᱨᱢᱟᱠᱥ ᱢᱮᱰᱤᱭᱟ ᱪᱷᱟᱯᱟ ᱯᱟᱨᱥᱟᱞ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ ᱾<ref name="Times of India">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Kapil-Sharma-beats-Salman-Khan-to-become-the-most-popular-TV-celebrity/articleshow/52341114.cms|title=Kapil Sharma beats Salman Khan to become the most popular TV personality|date=3 September 2016|work=The Times of India}}</ref> [[ᱯᱷᱳᱵᱚᱨᱥ]] ᱨᱮᱭᱟᱜ ᱑᱐᱐ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ-ᱟᱜ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛᱤᱭᱟᱹ ᱧᱩᱛᱩᱢᱟᱱ ᱦᱚᱲ ᱠᱚ ᱛᱟᱞᱟ ᱨᱮ ᱒᱐᱑᱖ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱚᱯᱤᱞ ᱥᱚᱨᱢᱟ ᱑᱑ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ-ᱟᱜ ᱟᱨ ᱒᱐᱑᱗ ᱨᱮ ᱫᱚ ᱑᱘ ᱜᱚᱴᱟᱝ-ᱟᱜ ᱴᱷᱟᱶ ᱮ ᱮᱥᱮᱫ ᱞᱮᱰ-ᱟ | <ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2016-celebrity-100/1587/1 |title=Forbes India Celebrity 100 |work=[[Forbes India]] |access-date=26 January 2018 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180127083912/https://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2016-celebrity-100/1587/1 |archive-date=27 January 2018 |url-status=dead }}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2017-celebrity-100/1665/all|title=2017 Celebrity 100 - Forbes India Magazine|website=Forbes India|language=en-US|access-date=22 December 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20171222162711/http://www.forbesindia.com/lists/2017-celebrity-100/1665/all|archive-date=22 December 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref> ᱒᱐᱑᱓ ᱨᱮ ᱩᱱᱤ ᱫᱚ, [[ᱥᱤᱹᱮᱱᱹᱮᱱᱹ-ᱟᱭᱹᱵᱤᱹᱮᱱᱹ]] ᱦᱚᱛᱮᱛᱮ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛ ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱢᱟᱨᱟᱝ ᱠᱚᱢᱮᱰᱤᱭᱟᱱ ᱢᱮᱱᱛᱮ ᱠᱚ ᱵᱟᱪᱷᱚᱱ ᱞᱮᱫᱮᱭᱟ ᱟᱨ ''[[ᱫᱤ ᱤᱠᱚᱱᱚᱢᱤᱠᱥ ᱴᱟᱭᱤᱢᱥ]]'' ᱦᱚᱛᱮᱛᱮ ᱥᱤᱧᱚᱛ ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱢᱟᱨᱟᱝ ᱯᱚᱨᱥᱚᱱᱟᱞᱤᱴᱤ ᱯᱮᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱛᱮᱥᱟᱨ ᱴᱷᱟᱝ-ᱮ ᱮᱥᱮᱫ ᱞᱮᱫ-ᱟ |<ref name="The Economic Times">[https://m.economictimes.com/slideshows/people/20-most-admired-people-in-india/kapil-sharma/slideshow/47260028.cms Kapil Sharma – 20 most admired people in India | ''The Economic Times''] (13 May 2015). Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref> ᱒᱐᱑᱔ ᱨᱮ ᱯᱨᱚᱝᱷᱟᱬ ᱢᱚᱱᱛᱨᱤ-ᱟᱜ ᱰᱟᱠᱨᱟ ᱞᱮᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱮᱛᱚᱦᱚᱵ ᱞᱮᱱ ''[[ᱥᱣᱚᱪᱷᱚ ᱵᱷᱟᱨᱚᱛ ᱚᱵᱷᱤᱭᱟᱱ]]'' ᱨᱮ ᱦᱚᱲ ᱠᱚ ᱥᱟᱯᱷ ᱥᱩᱛᱨᱟ. ᱛᱟᱦᱮᱱ ᱞᱟ.ᱜᱤᱱ ᱠᱚᱯᱤᱞ ᱥᱚᱨᱢᱟ ᱜᱮ ᱠᱟᱛᱷᱟ ᱯᱟᱨᱥᱟᱞ ᱞᱟ.ᱜᱤᱱ ᱠᱚ ᱵᱟᱪᱷᱟᱱ ᱞᱮᱫᱮᱭᱟ ᱾<ref name="timesofindia1">[https://m.timesofindia.com/tv/news/hindi/Kapil-Sharma-Will-do-my-best-for-Swachh-Bharat-Abhiyaan/articleshow/45640400.cms Kapil Sharma: Will do my best for Swachh Bharat Abhiyaan – ''The Times of India''] (25 December 2014). Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref> ᱥᱮᱯᱴᱮᱢᱵᱚᱨ ᱒᱐᱑᱕ ᱨᱮ ᱠᱚᱯᱤᱞ ᱟᱡᱟᱜ ᱥᱳ ᱤᱫᱤᱠᱟᱛᱮ ᱱᱚᱶᱟ ᱠᱟ.ᱢᱤ ᱨᱮ ᱟᱭᱢᱟ ᱜᱚᱲᱚ ᱠᱷᱟ.ᱛᱤᱨ ᱟᱡ ᱫᱚ ᱩᱱ ᱚᱠᱛᱚ ᱨᱤᱱᱤᱡ ᱯᱟᱨᱥᱮᱛ [[ᱯᱨᱚᱬᱚᱵᱽ ᱢᱩᱠᱷᱟᱨᱡᱤ]] ᱜᱮ [[ᱨᱟᱥᱴᱨᱚᱯᱚᱛᱤ ᱵᱷᱚᱵᱚᱱ]] ᱛᱮᱭ ᱱᱮᱣᱛᱟ ᱞᱮᱫᱮ ᱛᱟᱦᱮᱸᱫ ᱾<ref name="koimoi1">[https://m.koimoi.com/bollywood-news/kapil-sharma-to-meet-president-pranab-mukherjee KoiMoi – Kapil Sharma To Meet President Pranab Mukherjee] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150928213346/http://m.koimoi.com/bollywood-news/kapil-sharma-to-meet-president-pranab-mukherjee |date=28 September 2015 }}. M.koimoi.com (11 September 2015). Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref>

==Early and personal life==
Sharma was born in [[Amritsar, Punjab]], India as Kapil Punj.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://indianexpress.com/article/lifestyle/food-wine/kapil-sharma-on-amritsars-matthi-chhole-scotch-whisky-and-punjabis-and-dieting-the-foodie-interview-2820038/ |title=Comedian Kapil Sharma on Amritsar's matthi chhole, Scotch whisky, and Punjabis and dieting |publisher=[[The Indian Express]]|date=26 May 2016 }}</ref><ref name="TOIfacts"/> His father Jeetendra Kumar Punj was a head constable in Punjab Police, while his mother Janak Rani is a homemaker.<ref name=EarlyLife>{{cite news|title=Life has changed ever since, says comedian Kapil's family|url=https://www.hindustantimes.com/punjab/amritsar/life-has-changed-ever-since-says-comedian-kapil-s-family/article1-1173318.aspx|accessdate=18 December 2014|work=Hindustan Times}}</ref> His father was diagnosed with cancer in 1997 and died in 2004 at [[AIIMS]] in [[Delhi]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Kapil-Sharma-Seeing-my-daddy-suffer-in-his-last-days-I-prayed-to-God-to-take-him/articleshow/39944224.cms |title=Mr. Sharma: Seeing my daddy suffer in his last days, I prayed to God to take him |publisher=[[The Times of India]]}}</ref> He studied at Shri Ram Ashram Senior Secondary School, Amristar and Hindu College in Amritsar. He is featured in the list of prominent alumni of Apeejay College of Fine Arts, Jalandhar.<ref>{{cite web |title=Apeejay Prominent Alumni - Apeejay College of Fine Arts Jalandhar |url=https://acfa.apeejay.edu/alumni/prominent-alumni |website=acfa.apeejay.edu |accessdate=25 November 2019}}</ref> Sharma has a brother named Ashok Kumar Sharma, who is a Police constable and a sister named Pooja Pawan Devgan.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bollywoodlife.com/news-gossip/kapil-sharmas-personal-life-in-pictures/ |title=Kapil Sharma's personal life in pictures |publisher=Bollywood Life|date=2 April 2016 }}</ref>

Sharma and Ginnie met each other in 2005 and they were with each other for almost twelve years.<ref>{{url|https://www.pinkvilla.com/photos/kapil-sharma/kapil-sharma-and-ginni-chatrath-love-story-falling-love-getting-hitched-their-journey-one-kind-532697|Kapil Sharma and Ginni Chatrath Love Story: Falling in love to getting hitched, their journey is one of a kind}}</ref>

Sharma married Ginni Chatrath in [[Jalandhar]] on 12 December 2018<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/telly-talk/gossip/article/fans-congratulate-the-newlyweds-kapil-sharma-and-ginni-chatrath-on-twitter-read-tweets-tv-news/330219|title=Fans congratulate the newlyweds Kapil Sharma and Ginni Chatrath on Twitter - read tweets {{!}} TV News|website=www.timesnownews.com|language=en-GB|access-date=12 December 2018}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/telly-talk/gossip/article/kapil-sharma-and-ginni-chatrath-are-now-married-view-photo/330054|title=Kapil Sharma and Ginni Chatrath are now married|website=www.timesnownews.com|language=en-GB|access-date=12 December 2018}}</ref> They had a daughter on 10 December 2019.<ref>{{cite news |title=Kapil Sharma and wife Ginni Chatrath blessed with a baby girl |url=https://www.indiatoday.in/television/celebrity/story/kapil-sharma-and-wife-ginni-chatrath-blessed-with-a-baby-girl-1626899-2019-12-10 |accessdate=10 December 2019 |work=India Today |date=10 December 2019 |language=en}}</ref>

==Career==
Sharma rose to fame after winning the comedy reality television show ''[[The Great Indian Laughter Challenge]]'' in 2007, for which he won a cash prize of [[Indian rupee|INR]] ₹10 lakh.<ref name="TimesofIndia">{{cite news |title= Kapil Sharma plays the 'Traffic monitor' at India Gate |url= https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tv/news-and-gossip/Kapil-Sharma-plays-the-Traffic-monitor-at-India-Gate/articleshow/22334306.cms |work=The Times of India |date= 26 September 2013}}</ref> He had previously worked in the Punjabi show ''Hasde Hasaande Ravo'' on MH One channel.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.thequint.com/entertainment/2016/04/02/funny-punjabi-punjab-amritsar-comedian-television-odd-jobs |title=5 Things You Didn't Know About Birthday Boy Kapil Sharma |publisher=Quint|date=2 April 2016 }}</ref> Sharma has stated that he moved to Mumbai in order to become a singer.<ref name="TOIfacts">{{cite news |title=Name and fame - Kapil Sharma: Lesser known facts |url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/photo-features/kapil-sharma-lesser-known-facts/name-and-fame/photostory/61130448.cms |accessdate=5 January 2020 |work=The Times of India }}</ref>

[[File:Prabhudeva, Sonu Sood, Shahid Kapoor, Sonakshi Sinha and Kapil Sharma on the sets of Comedy Nights with Kapil.jpg|Sharma (standing) on the sets of ''Comedy Nights with Kapil'' in 2013|right|thumb]]
He participated in [[Sony Entertainment Television (India)|Sony]]'s ''[[Comedy Circus]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.siasat.com/english/news/parvati-singhal-kapil-crown-comedy-king |title=Parvati Singhal, Kapil crown Comedy King |publisher=Siasat |date=29 August 2010 |accessdate=3 March 2014}}</ref> and went on to win six seasons of the show.<ref>[https://m.timesofindia.com/tv/news/hindi/Kapil-wins-yet-another-season-of-Comedy-Circus/articleshow/11131528.cms Kapil wins yet another season of Comedy Circus – The Times of India]. M.timesofindia.com (16 December 2011). Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref> He also hosted the dance reality show ''[[Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa (season 6)|Jhalak Dikhhla Jaa Season 6]]''<ref>[https://forbesindia.com/celebprofile/kapil-sharma/186 Kapil Sharma] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20141225093429/https://forbesindia.com/celebprofile/kapil-sharma/186 |date=25 December 2014 }}. Forbesindia.com. Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref> and another comedy show ''[[Chhote Miyan]]''.<ref>{{cite news|author=Aparna Banerji |url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/2009/20090724/jplus.htm#3 |title=Lady laughter sends T-town rolling |work=Tribune India |date=24 July 2009 |accessdate=21 July 2014}}</ref><ref name=toi13>{{cite news| title = Daily soaps weren't creatively satisfying: Manish Paul | url = https://articles.timesofindia.indiatimes.com/2013-08-11/tv/41293838_1_kapil-sharma-manish-paul-humour|date=11 August 2013 | accessdate = 16 August 2013 | work = [[The Times of India]] }}</ref> Sharma was seen as a contestant in the show ''[[Ustaadon Ka Ustaad]]'' in 2008. In 2013, Kapil launched his own show, ''[[Comedy Nights with Kapil]]'', under his banner K9 Productions on [[Colors (TV channel)|Colors]].

At the CNN-IBN Indian of the Year awards 2013, Sharma was felicitated with the Indian of the Year award in the entertainment category by veteran actor [[Amol Palekar]].<ref name="tr">{{cite news|author=Wadehra, Randeep |url=https://www.tribuneindia.com/2007/20070916/spectrum/main3.htm|title=The Great Punjabi Challenge|date=16 September 2007|work=[[The Tribune (Chandigarh)|The Tribune]]}}</ref> During the [[2014 Indian general election|2014 Lok Sabha Elections]], he was appointed the Brand Ambassador by the Delhi Election Commission.<ref>[https://news.biharprabha.com/2014/04/comedian-kapil-sharma-to-be-brand-ambassador-for-delhi-poll/ Comedian Kapil Sharma to be brand ambassador for Delhi poll]. News.biharprabha.com (5 April 2014). Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref>

Sharma was the co-host of the [[60th Filmfare Awards|60th]] [[Filmfare Awards]] in 2015 along with [[Karan Johar]].<ref>Narayan, Girija. (5 February 2015) [https://www.filmibeat.com/television/news/2015/when-kapil-sharma-stole-karan-johars-thunder-at-filmfare-awards-2015-172887.html When Kapil Sharma Stole Karan Johar's Thunder At Filmfare Awards 2015!]. Filmibeat. Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref> He was the presenter for the fourth season of [[Celebrity Cricket League]], 2014.<ref>Narayan, Girija. (20 January 2014) [https://www.filmibeat.com/television/news/2014/kapil-sharma-host-ccl-2014-launch-event-had-sachin-dhanush-venkatesh-130122.html Kapil Sharma To Host CCL 2014; Launch Event With Sachin, Dhanush, Venkatesh...]. Filmibeat. Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref> He appeared as a guest on the opening episode of the eighth season of the Indian television game show ''[[Kaun Banega Crorepati]]''<ref>{{cite news|url=http://indiatoday.intoday.in/story/kapil-sharma-amitabh-bachchan-first-guest-kbc-8/1/374806.html |title=Kapil Sharma is Amitabh Bachchan's first guest on KBC 8 |publisher=India Today |date=30 July 2014 |accessdate=30 July 2014}}</ref> and also as a celebrity guest on ''[[The Anupam Kher Show]]''.<ref>Narayan, Girija. (19 August 2014) [https://www.filmibeat.com/television/news/2014/read-emotional-revelations-kapil-sharma-made-the-anupam-kher-show-157089.html#slide63377 Emotional Revelations Kapil Sharma Made On The Anupam Kher Show!]. Filmibeat. Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref> He also appeared as a guest in [[Koffee with Karan|Koffee With Karan]] in 2017.

Sharma made his [[Bollywood]] debut as the male lead in the movie ''[[Kis Kisko Pyaar Karoon]]'', a romantic-comedy directed by [[Abbas Mustan]] opposite four actresses, [[Elli Avram]], [[Manjari Phadnis]], [[Simran Kaur Mundi]] and [[Sai Lokur]].<ref name="indiatimes1">{{cite news|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/hindi/bollywood/news/Kapil-Sharmas-film-goes-on-floor/articleshow/45078735.cms|title=Kapil Sharma's film goes on floor|date=8 November 2014|work=The Times of India}}</ref> The film was released on 25 September 2015 to mixed reviews from critics, but did record-breaking opening day business for a debut.<ref name="m.indiatoday.in">{{cite news | title = Kapil Sharma's film sets box office on fire | url = https://m.indiatoday.in/story/kis-kisko-pyaar-karoon-collection-kapil-sharmas-debut-film-sets-box-office-on-fire-in-its-opening-weekend/1/484955.html | access-date = 26 January 2018 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20171114040332/http://m.indiatoday.in/story/kis-kisko-pyaar-karoon-collection-kapil-sharmas-debut-film-sets-box-office-on-fire-in-its-opening-weekend/1/484955.html | archive-date = 14 November 2017 | url-status = dead }}</ref><ref name="indiatimes1"/><ref name=opening>[https://m.ibtimes.co.in/kis-kisko-pyaar-karoon-opening-day-box-office-collection-kapil-sharmas-movie-smashes-records-648159 'Kis Kisko Pyaar Karoon' opening day box office collection: Kapil Sharma's movie smashes records; Beats 'Baby' 1st day business] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20150927142004/https://m.ibtimes.co.in/kis-kisko-pyaar-karoon-opening-day-box-office-collection-kapil-sharmas-movie-smashes-records-648159 |date=27 September 2015 }}. M.ibtimes.co.in. Retrieved on 27 September 2015.</ref>

After the end of ''[[Comedy Nights with Kapil]]'', Sharma signed a contract with Sony TV for a new show called ''[[The Kapil Sharma Show]]''. Its last episode was aired on 24 January 2016. After that he started working on [[Sony Entertainment Television (India)|Sony Entertainment Television]] for ''The Kapil Sharma Show'' under his K9 Productions. ''The Kapil Sharma Show'' started airing on 23 April 2016 and received a positive response from the viewers.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://m.timesofindia.com/tv/news/hindi/The-Kapil-Sharma-Show-tops-the-non-fiction-category/articleshow/52906878.cms|title=The Kapil Sharma Show tops the non-fiction category – TOI Mobile – The Times of India Mobile Site|work=timesofindia.com|accessdate=6 September 2016}}</ref><ref name="auto">{{Cite web|url=https://thekapilsharmashowtv.com|title=The Kapil Sharma Show Watch Full Episodes Online Sony TV Know About
|website=The Kapil Sharma Show TV|language=en-US|access-date=8 April 2016}}</ref>

As of December 2016, he has signed two movies and is currently working on them.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/tv/news/hindi/Kiku-Sunil-Grover-wish-Kapil-Sharma-luck-for-his-new-journey-in-Punjab/articleshow/55666069.cms|title=Kiku, Sunil Grover wish Kapil Sharma luck for his new journey in Punjab|work=India Tv}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.indiatvnews.com/entertainment/bollywood-kapil-sharma-second-movie-details-356670|title=Apparently, Kapil Sharma can't wait for second movie to start; details here|work=India Tv|date=15 November 2016}}</ref> Also he has renewed his contract with Sony Entertainment Television for ''The Kapil Sharma Show'',<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://news.liveurlifehere.com/in/know-much-kapil-sharma-charge-contract-renewal-sony-tv.html|title=Do you know how much Kapil Sharma charge for contract renewal with Sony TV|date=5 December 2016|newspaper=Liveurlifehere News|access-date=22 December 2016}}</ref> which began airing on 29 December 2018.

His second movie ''[[Firangi]]'' was released on 1 December 2017. Directed by Rajiev Dhingra, ''Firangi'' is a historical drama film set in the year 1920.

His next show was launched on 25 March 2018 stating as ''[[Family Time With Kapil Sharma]]'' which was ended on 1 April after only 3 episodes. In 2018, he produced a [[Punjabi language|Punjabi]] movie named ''[[Son of Manjeet Singh]]'' which was released on 12 October 2018. 
His show ''The Kapil Sharma Show'' was aired with a new season on 29 December 2018, produced by [[Salman Khan]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.timesnownews.com/entertainment/telly-talk/gossip/article/sunil-grover-reveals-salman-khan-is-producing-the-new-season-of-the-kapil-sharma-show-tv-news/328642|title=Salman Khan is the producer of the new season of The Kapil Sharma Show, reveals Sunil Grover|work=Times Now News|date=10 December 2018}}</ref>

==Activism==
Sharma has been known for his efforts in promoting animal rights. He and the cast of ''[[Comedy Nights with Kapil]]'' appeared in a [[PETA]] campaign to promote adoption of homeless cats and dogs.<ref>[https://indianexpress.com/article/entertainment/television/comedy-nights-with-kapil-cast-in-new-peta-campaign/ ‘Comedy Nights With Kapil’ cast in new PETA campaign]. ''The Indian Express'' (8 July 2015). Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref> In July 2014, he adopted a homeless dog, a retired police dog from [[Mumbai]]. He has also campaigned to save tortured elephants across the country.<ref>[https://m.timesofindia.com/tv/news/hindi/10-reasons-why-we-love-Kapil-Sharma/articleshow/47816657.cms 10 reasons why we love Kapil Sharma – ''The Times of India''] (26 June 2015). Retrieved on 16 September 2015.</ref>
Sharma was nominated for the ''[[Swachh Bharat Abhiyan]]'' by the Indian Prime Minister [[Narendra Modi]] for which he campaigned and regularly promotes on his show.<ref name="timesofindia1"/><ref>{{Cite news|last=IANS|url=https://www.business-standard.com/article/news-ians/pm-names-comedian-kapil-sharma-for-swachh-bharat-abhiyaan-114122500335_1.html|title=PM names comedian Kapil Sharma for Swachh Bharat Abhiyaan|date=25 December 2014|work=Business Standard India|access-date=12 March 2020}}</ref>

